(self.webpackChunkLunarVim_com=self.webpackChunkLunarVim_com||[]).push([[792],{2643:(e,t,o)=>{"use strict";o.r(t),o.d(t,{data:()=>i});const i={key:"v-521e541a",path:"/configuration/disable-compe.html",title:"Disable tab completion",lang:"en-US",frontmatter:{},excerpt:"",headers:[],filePathRelative:"configuration/disable-compe.md",git:{updatedTime:162749295e4,contributors:[]}}},2820:(e,t,o)=>{"use strict";o.r(t),o.d(t,{default:()=>c});const i=(0,o(6252).uE)('<h1 id="disable-tab-completion" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#disable-tab-completion" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Disable tab completion</h1><p>When writing code pressing <code>TAB</code> triggers autocomplete. But in simple text files hitting tab should insert a <code>TAB</code> character. LunarVim turns off tab autocompletion for markdown and txt files. To disable autocompletion for other filetypes modify <code>lvim.builtin.compe.exclude_filetypes</code> in your <code>lv-config.lua</code>.</p><div class="language-text ext-text line-numbers-mode"><pre class="language-text"><code>lvim.builtin.compe.exclude_filetypes = { &quot;md&quot;, &quot;markdown&quot;, &quot;mdown&quot;, &quot;mkd&quot;, &quot;mkdn&quot;, &quot;mdwn&quot;, &quot;text&quot;, &quot;txt&quot; },\n</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div><p><code>Control</code>+<code>space</code> will still trigger completion. This is useful for autocompleting emoji in text files. (type <code>:</code> and hit <code>control</code>+<code>space</code> or <code>TAB</code> to cycle through emoji)</p><p>Compe-enabled autocomplete was not removed from markdown and text files, just the <code>TAB</code> keymap. To trigger autocomplete press <code>Control</code>+<code>Space</code>.</p><p>Add this to your lv-config.lua to opt out entirely.</p><div class="language-text ext-text line-numbers-mode"><pre class="language-text"><code>lvim.builtin.compe.exclude_filetypes = {  }\n</code></pre><div class="line-numbers"><span class="line-number">1</span><br></div></div>',7),c={render:function(e,t){return i}}}}]);